Date: 16 Dec 1998 13:58:23 -0700
From: Matt Taylor <mtaylor@cadvision.com>

Re your comment about American horsemeat coming from 'spent' horses going
direct to slaughter.
Not so.
The American (and Canadian) horsemeat business is concentrated amongst a
very few operators. I believe 65% of Canadian horsemeat exports come from 1
operator who has 3 plants, I think. These big operators 'feed' horses, just
like cattle. And a lot of the meat comes from younger animals. There are a
couple of feedlots here in Alberta, and others in Kansas and Texas that I
know of though others exist too.
Don't know if this affects your thoughts on _Trichinella_, but I thought
I'd let you know in the event it's relevant.
Enjoy this list-server very much. Thank you for your work and comments as a
moderator!
--
Matt Taylor
e-mail: mtaylor@cadvision.com
